Weeks 1-2: Foundations of Data Science
Week 1: Introduction to Data Science and Python Basics

Day 1-3: Overview of data science, roles, and common tools. Install Jupyter Notebook or Google Colab.
Day 4-7: Python basics (data types, loops, conditionals, functions).
Projects: Basic data manipulation using Python lists, dictionaries, and functions.

Week 2: Data Structures & Algorithms (Python)

Day 8-9: Understanding arrays, linked lists, stacks, queues.
Day 10-12: Sorting algorithms (merge sort, quicksort) and their time complexities.
Day 13-14: Implement simple algorithms like binary search.
Projects: Solve basic data structure problems.
